<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="ring-v">ring <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /rɪŋ/    美 /rɪŋ/  </p>
<p>(rang, rung) vi &amp; vt</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使钟、铃) 鸣响；敲 (钟)；按 (铃)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>ring an alarm 
敲起警钟</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The bell rang. 
铃响了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Someone is ringing at the door. 
有人在按门铃。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>打电话 (给)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>ring for a taxi 
打电话叫出租车</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Can I <strong>ring back</strong> later? 
我过一会儿再回电话好吗？</p><footer>人教⑧ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll ring you this evening. 
我今晚给你打电话。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="ring-off">ring off</h3>
<p>1.<strong>挂断电话</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="ring-up">ring up</h3>
<p>1.<strong>打电话 (给)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll ring him up again. 
我会再打电话给他。</p><footer>人教⑧ – 3</footer></div></div>